      • appendToListProp

        public void appendToListProp(java.lang.String key,
                             java.lang.String value)
        Description copied from class: State
        Appends the input value to a list property that can be retrieved with State.getPropAsList(java.lang.String).

        List properties are internally stored as comma separated strings. Adding a value that contains commas (for example "a,b,c") will essentially add multiple values to the property ("a", "b", and "c"). This is similar to the way that Configuration works.

        Overrides:
        appendToListProp in class State
        Parameters:
        key - property key
        value - property value (if it includes commas, it will be split by the commas).
